    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5847" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λί̄ς</span></b>  (3), dat. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λῑτί</span>, acc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λῖτα</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">linen</span> cloth, used as cover for a
          seat, <i><span class="en">Od. 10.353</span></i>; or for a chariot
          when not in use, <i><span class="en">Il. 8.441</span></i>; also as
          shroud for the dead, <i><span class="en">Il. 18.352</span></i>; and
          to cover a cinerary urn, <i><span class="en">Il.
          23.254</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
